Object Oriented programming



CLASSES AND OBJECTS

Objects : entities in real world

Classes: group of these entities.

.     ------->    attributes (properties)
.   /
Class                     +
.   \
.     -------->   Functions (behaviour)
.
Ex:



.          ------->    attributes---> colour (String value init)
.        /
Class Pen                     +
.        \
.          -------->         Fn's---> Change color()  
.                                       //This fn's chnage string value of color attribute 

 

Class               Attribute               functions

Pen             Color: (String blue)       Set Color();
                
.                Tip:    5(int)             Set Tip();

.                                       //These fn's chnage  value of their attribute 



Points to remember:---

-->  Class Name : Always starts with capital letters.
.    Fn's 'Name :  Always starts with small letters
.
.            Class Name :--   Capital letter.
.            Fn Name    :--   Small letter.
.
.            Ex: 
.                public class OOPS{}
.
.                public class A_Class_Name{}                            


--> When a java program is run it first looks for public class
    then in public class looks main Fn's inside that public class


--> Best Pratice to write them at top of other class & object

.        Java Program ---->  public class ----->  main fn ()

